<div class="comments-body">
<p>Yep, it works just fine. The only supported hosts are W2K Pro and XP Pro, so I expect that they might give you a bit of grief if you called in for support. However, any W2K, XP, or W2K3 works fine (and yes, I've tried it on XP Home with no problems).</p>

<p>The Virtual Server product (in beta now, or soon) is what they've designed to run on servers. I expect that's why they limited the "supported" configs to W2K and XP Pro. Kinda lame, when you think about it, since devs are at least as likely to be running some server OS as a Pro OS, and this is really a heavily developer targetted product.</p>

